# Simplify Log — Issue #34

## Three-Agent Review

### Code Reuse Review
- CLEAN: All shared MCP utilities (ok, error, catchErrors, requireString, requireNumber, runServer) correctly used
- CLEAN: Server definition structure matches established pattern
- CLEAN: Test structure follows existing conventions
- Minor: No `optionalNumber()` helper exists — inline handling of `last_n` is acceptable

### Code Quality Review
- `checkEnabled()` per-call vs `onInit()` — intentional design (hot-toggleable gate, not startup check)
- `envMapping: {}` — intentional (DARK_FACTORY_ENABLED doesn't map to MessageContext)
- Redundant timestamp — FIXED (unified to single Date object)
- KDL escaping concern — false positive (shell escaping within KDL string is correct)

### Efficiency Review
- Head-sniffing reads entire file — FIXED (bounded fs.openSync/readSync for 5KB)
- TOCTOU existsSync checks — FIXED (try-catch on actual operations)
- N+1 stat calls — acceptable (small directory, infrequent tool calls)
- Full JSONL parse then slice — acceptable (conversation files are bounded by Claude session length)

## Changes Made (3c1a914)
1. Replaced `fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8').slice(0, 5000)` with bounded `fs.openSync`/`fs.readSync` (reads only 5KB from disk)
2. Replaced `fs.existsSync(metadataPath)` + `fs.readFileSync` with try-catch
3. Replaced `fs.existsSync(claudeDir)` + `fs.readdirSync` with try-catch on readdirSync
4. Unified `Date.now()` and `new Date().toISOString()` into single `new Date()` object

